The paper deals with properties of binary matrices and their rank functions, which are topics that are commonly studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also presents a concrete characterization of a family of matrices based on their binary rank, which is a topic that falls under computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper uses the Augmentation property to construct families of matrices with gaps between their real and binary/boolean rank, which is a topic that falls under machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG).
